external_knowledge:
- Navigators refer to users executing the queries; 
- Cosmic seas represent the types of databases (DBMS); 
- Voyages refer to the types of queries (SELECT, INSERT, etc.); 
- Charting their courses implies planning time for queries; 
- Total time traveled is the total execution time of the queries.

sql:
SELECT dbid, COUNT(*) AS num_queries
FROM queries
GROUP BY dbid;

external_knowledge:
- "problematic queries" refers to queries that failed;
- "last month of the year" means December 2022;
- 'dbid' represents the database ID where the query was executed.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT u.username
FROM users u
JOIN queries q ON u.userid = q.userid
WHERE q.total_plan_time > (
    SELECT AVG(total_plan_time) FROM queries
);

SELECT AVG(qe.rows) AS avg_rows
FROM query_executions qe
WHERE qe.execution_start_time >= DATE('now', '-1 day');

SELECT query, FLOOR(total_plan_time) AS rounded_total_plan_time
FROM queries
WHERE query_id = 1;

SELECT AVG(total_exec_time) AS average_execution_time
FROM query_executions
WHERE query_id = 1;
